definition.value: Psychogenic non-epileptic seizures (PNES) are not abnormal perceptions or abnormal beliefs/judgments, nor are they epileptic attacks. They are behaviors that simulate epileptic attacks, not fully consciously.

label.value: Decreased circulating terminal complement component concentration

definition.value: Abnormal activity of coagulation factor IX. Factor IX, which itself is activated by factor Xa or factor VIIa to form factor IXa, activates factor X into factor Xa.

label.value: Renal interstitial IgG4+ plasma cell infiltration

definition.value: Anomalous physical appearance (color, cloudiness, clarity) or odor of urine.
An elevated concentration of free thyroxine (fT4) in the blood circulation.
A reduced concentration of free thyroxine (fT4) in the blood circulation.
Absence or underdevelopment of the thyroid gland.

label.value: Abnormal TSH response to thyrotrophin-releasing hormone stimulation test

definition.value: Thyrotrophin-releasing hormone (TRH) is a hypothalamic tripeptide synthesized by, stored within, and released from the hypothalamus. It stimulates the synthesis and release of thyroid-stimulating hormone (TSH) from the anterior pituitary gland. Following administration of exogenous TRH, a transient increase in serum TSH is expected. This term refers to an abnormal response in the TRH stimulation test.

label.value: Absent TSH response to thyrotrophin-releasing hormone stimulation test
Reduced TSH response to thyrotrophin-releasing hormone stimulation test

definition.value: A lower than normal TSH response to thyrotrophin-releasing hormone stimulation test.

Any deviation from a count of antral follicles that is normal for age. Antral follicles appear as small fluid-filled sacs that contain an immature egg. Antral follicle count can be measured (usually on day 2-5 of the menstrual cycle) by transvaginal ultrasound. The number of antral follicles may reflect ovarian reserve.
An increased level of a branched chain family amino acid in the urine.

definition.value: An increased level in the urine of an alpha-amino acid which is not a member of the group of 23 proteinogenic amino acids.

label.value: Increased proteinogenic amino acid level in urine

definition.value: An elevated level of a proteinogenic amino acid in the urine. These are the 23 alpha-amino acids that are precursors to proteins, and are incorporated into proteins during translation. The group includes the 20 amino acids encoded by the nuclear genes of eukaryotes together with selenocysteine, pyrrolysine, and N-formylmethionine.
